00:03:59.028 --> 00:04:01.920
<v Morgan> When you put
a form on your website,

00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:05.250
the very first thing you need
to do is to ask yourself,

00:04:05.250 --> 00:04:06.800
why are you building a form?

00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:10.970
How can you build the form
to meet not only your needs

00:04:10.970 --> 00:04:12.900
but also your users' needs?

00:04:14.180 --> 00:04:17.530
So often,
accessibility is an afterthought.

00:04:17.530 --> 00:04:20.400
We build a website, and then we
test it with keyboard navigation

00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:22.490
and a screen reader and we
fix the problems we have

00:04:22.490 --> 00:04:24.890
and we call it a day.

00:04:24.890 --> 00:04:27.660
You should really start
thinking about accessibility

00:04:27.660 --> 00:04:32.470
before you even create a form
because they are so important.

00:04:32.470 --> 00:04:34.920
You want to build the
form, not just the code,

00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:38.280
but also the form questions
in the form visual design

00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:41.120
with your users' needs in
mind from the very beginning.

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:47.230
In addition to accessibility, you
also want to think about usability,

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:50.207
and not just for users
with disabilities,

00:04:50.208 --> 00:04:52.120
but for all of your users.

00:04:52.120 --> 00:04:55.350
Accessibility and usability are
very closely linked together,

00:04:55.350 --> 00:04:59.630
and it's not just about assistive
tools like keyboard navigation

00:04:59.630 --> 00:05:00.990
and screen in meters.

00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:05.900
You want all of your users to easily
understand and fill out your forms.

00:05:07.240 --> 00:05:09.793
If you ask yourself
from the beginning,

00:05:09.794 --> 00:05:11.580
why you're building a form,

00:05:11.580 --> 00:05:14.750
this is going to impact
how you build the form.

00:05:14.750 --> 00:05:18.970
For example, you're going to want to
build an e-commerce form differently

00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:20.920
from the job application.

00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:25.020
On an e-commerce form, you want it to
be as short and as easy as possible.

00:05:25.020 --> 00:05:28.540
You don't want users to have time
to second guess their purchases,

00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:32.450
you want them to give you your
money, and submit the form.

00:05:33.780 --> 00:05:37.220
If your form is a job
application, users are willing

00:05:37.220 --> 00:05:39.440
to put some more work
into a job application,

00:05:39.440 --> 00:05:43.280
so it can be a more complex
form, but you still don't want

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:46.380
to make it too difficult for them.

00:05:46.380 --> 00:05:49.440
Different forms have different
usability requirements, and you want

00:05:49.440 --> 00:05:51.020
to think about that
from the beginning.

00:05:53.100 --> 00:05:56.720
You need to think about what
information you actually need

00:05:56.720 --> 00:05:58.120
from your users.

00:05:58.120 --> 00:06:01.420
Do you really need all
of those form fields?

00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:03.660
Once you start asking
questions, it's really tempting

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:06.320
to keep asking more,
but you want to make sure

00:06:06.320 --> 00:06:09.640
that you're really only asking
users for the information

00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:11.220
you actually need.

00:06:11.220 --> 00:06:13.067
For instance, on contact forms,

00:06:13.068 --> 00:06:15.510
contact forms often
have phone numbers.

00:06:16.910 --> 00:06:20.330
Do you really need that phone
number on the contact form,

00:06:20.330 --> 00:06:23.120
or demographic information?

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:26.490
We often want to know as much
as we can about our users' age,

00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:28.920
experience level,
how they found us.

00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:31.530
A lot of that information
isn't strictly necessary,

00:06:31.530 --> 00:06:34.010
and it just makes the
form longer for the user.

00:06:35.100 --> 00:06:38.020
On the other hand, maybe you do need
that information, and that's fine.

00:06:38.020 --> 00:06:41.110
Ask for it if you need it,
but just be aware that users

00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:46.000
might be hesitant to share even
personal information like gender

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.440
or marital status, or race.

00:06:48.440 --> 00:06:52.020
Only ask for that
information if you need it.

00:06:52.020 --> 00:06:54.533
If you do need that
kind of information,

00:06:54.534 --> 00:06:58.815
make it clear to your users why
you are requesting the information

00:06:58.816 --> 00:07:00.920
and how you're going to use it.

00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:04.380
For example, if you are asking
for demographic information,

00:07:04.380 --> 00:07:09.870
such as race or gender, make it
clear why you need that information

00:07:09.870 --> 00:07:11.210
and how you're going to use it.

00:07:12.450 --> 00:07:16.850
Another example is a
phone number field.

00:07:16.850 --> 00:07:19.140
If you are asking
for a phone number,

00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:23.050
you should probably clarify
whether you plan to use that number

00:07:23.050 --> 00:07:26.410
for phone calls or for
text, because some users

00:07:26.410 --> 00:07:28.550
might actually give you a
different phone number depending on

00:07:28.550 --> 00:07:30.690
how you're going to use it.

00:07:30.690 --> 00:07:34.760
The more information you
give your users about

00:07:34.760 --> 00:07:37.780
why you're asking these questions,
the more likely they are

00:07:37.780 --> 00:07:39.660
to be willing to
answer those questions.

00:07:42.350 --> 00:07:44.910
You also want to think about
the easiest way for users

00:07:44.910 --> 00:07:48.250
to give you the information
you need and what kind of

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:51.680
form inputs are easiest
for them to use.

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:58.130
For instance, if you are asking for
categories, you might have a list

00:07:58.130 --> 00:08:02.080
of 100 categories, and you
should think about, is it easier

00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:04.850
for your users to read
through that big long list

00:08:04.850 --> 00:08:07.890
and pick out the correct ones,
or would it be easier for them

00:08:07.890 --> 00:08:10.810
to just type in
their own categories?

00:08:10.810 --> 00:08:14.150
If they're typing in their own
categories, the data you get

00:08:14.150 --> 00:08:17.810
might not be as clean,
but you'll actually get better data

00:08:17.810 --> 00:08:21.200
because it's going to
be easier for your users

00:08:21.200 --> 00:08:23.620
to fill out the
correct information.

00:08:23.620 --> 00:08:25.870
On the other hand,
if it is really important

00:08:25.870 --> 00:08:31.880
that users give exactly the
categories that you have in mind,

00:08:31.880 --> 00:08:34.860
then a drop-down probably
is the better choice.

00:08:35.980 --> 00:08:38.450
You just need to think through,
is it easier for your users

00:08:38.450 --> 00:08:41.040
to read through a long list or
to type in their own answer.

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:46.080
Once you've thought
about these questions,

00:08:46.080 --> 00:08:47.860
what information do you
need from your users,

00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:51.400
and what's the easiest way for
them to give you that information?

00:08:51.400 --> 00:08:53.580
Now you're ready to
start building your form.

00:08:53.580 --> 00:08:56.620
I'll turn it over to Rian to
talk some more about usability.

00:08:56.620 --> 00:09:01.460
<v Rian> Form usability
or user experience.

00:09:01.460 --> 00:09:06.150
How to help your user fill out
a form as easy as possible.

00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:08.480
The last thing you
want, that users leave

00:09:08.480 --> 00:09:12.010
because a form is too
complicated or not trustworthy.

00:09:14.450 --> 00:09:16.980
Very important is
to be predictable.

00:09:18.830 --> 00:09:22.620
For example, make sure the
user has everything they need

00:09:22.620 --> 00:09:26.540
at hand before they start
filling out the form.

00:09:26.540 --> 00:09:30.760
For example, a credit card
number, passport, an order number,

00:09:30.760 --> 00:09:33.760
or other documents or
information they might need.

00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:38.520
Do you have a timer on your form?

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:41.370
For example, for security reasons?

00:09:41.370 --> 00:09:45.300
Don't cause a panic, "Oh,
my I don't have that time.

00:09:45.300 --> 00:09:46.300
I cannot do this."

00:09:46.300 --> 00:09:48.610
Tick-tock, tick-tock,
the user panics.

00:09:50.930 --> 00:09:55.110
Inform them in advance there
will be a timer and tell them

00:09:55.110 --> 00:09:57.290
why there is a timer.

00:09:57.290 --> 00:10:02.120
Inform them about the time
they have and give them a way

00:10:02.120 --> 00:10:05.520
to extend that time,
not everybody is that quick.

00:10:09.090 --> 00:10:13.030
As Morgan already told, only
ask what you really, really need

00:10:13.030 --> 00:10:17.460
to know, but even then
that can be quite a lot.

00:10:17.460 --> 00:10:19.750
Do you have long form?

00:10:19.750 --> 00:10:27.550
Break it up in steps, each step a
topic, tell how many steps there are.

00:10:29.720 --> 00:10:33.970
Name each step and tell
what will happen next.

00:10:33.970 --> 00:10:36.990
Let users know how much
they still need to fill out.

00:10:38.640 --> 00:10:43.350
For everybody, especially people
with anxiety, this is helpful

00:10:43.350 --> 00:10:44.350
and reassuring.

00:10:46.260 --> 00:10:50.090
At the bottom of each step,
provide clear navigation,

00:10:51.840 --> 00:10:56.890
not just back and next
but back to step two.

00:10:56.890 --> 00:11:02.380
The next step, step four is
student information, for example.

00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:07.060
Then people are reassured
they are doing the right thing

00:11:07.060 --> 00:11:11.820
and they also can go back and
check what has been filled out,

00:11:11.820 --> 00:11:13.350
so be predictable.

00:11:16.660 --> 00:11:20.500
Don't put the burden of
your problem on the user

00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:21.750
and that's what happens a lot.

00:11:23.140 --> 00:11:27.040
We all hate spam
informs, don't you?

00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:31.810
Maybe accept the people who sent
you spam, so what do you do?

00:11:31.810 --> 00:11:35.850
You put the burden of
preventing spam on your user.

00:11:35.850 --> 00:11:39.230
"Hey, you, prove you're a
human with good intentions."

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:42.070
For example, you add a CAPTCHA.

00:11:43.980 --> 00:11:47.810
This is an example I saw in
the world is actually a CAPTCHA

00:11:48.940 --> 00:11:54.870
from Google version 2, please click
each image containing a smiling dog,

00:11:56.180 --> 00:11:57.180
really.

00:11:57.920 --> 00:12:02.260
I'm a cat person, smiling dog
is really a problem for me

00:12:02.260 --> 00:12:07.390
and what about people with autism
who have difficulties reading emotion

00:12:07.390 --> 00:12:08.390
from a face?

00:12:09.640 --> 00:12:13.830
I also must be able to
recognize you as school buses.

00:12:13.830 --> 00:12:14.350
Really?

00:12:14.350 --> 00:12:17.390
I'm from Europe, what do I know
about you as a school buses?

00:12:19.010 --> 00:12:22.280
Google CAPTCHA version
3 is user-friendly

00:12:22.280 --> 00:12:25.350
but maybe has some privacy issues.

00:12:26.820 --> 00:12:31.290
A rising star is a turnstile who
claims to be a user-friendly,

00:12:31.290 --> 00:12:34.750
privacy-preserving,
alternative to CAPTCHA.

00:12:34.750 --> 00:12:40.260
I haven't researched it but which
option you choose, do your research

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:45.020
and take accessibility, GDPR,
and usability into account.

00:12:47.680 --> 00:12:53.270
