00:16:25.590 --> 00:16:29.360
and honestly, out of the
box, a lot of them are ugly.

00:16:29.360 --> 00:16:32.350
It's natural to want to change
the appearance of your forms

00:16:32.350 --> 00:16:35.590
to make them more
consistent across browsers,

00:16:35.590 --> 00:16:38.330
to make them more pleasing to the
eye, and to make them look better

00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:39.680
with the rest of your website.

00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:44.990
You need to be careful when
you restyle form elements

00:16:44.990 --> 00:16:48.240
and make sure you don't
change the design so much

00:16:48.240 --> 00:16:50.930
that users can't recognize them.

00:16:50.930 --> 00:16:54.150
You want to make sure
that your designed

00:16:54.150 --> 00:16:57.980
form inputs still feel familiar
and intuitive so users know

00:16:57.980 --> 00:16:59.800
how to interact with them.

00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:03.410
For example, this is a demo
I found on CodePen that shows

00:17:03.410 --> 00:17:07.090
how to style radio
buttons and checkboxes.

00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:11.260
You can see that for both
radio buttons and checkboxes,

00:17:11.260 --> 00:17:14.110
they're using both
squares and circles.

00:17:15.680 --> 00:17:19.390
Then they have these other
shapes like this rounded square

00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:25.360
and this diamond and it's not
obvious from looking at these

00:17:25.360 --> 00:17:28.130
whether you are allowed
to select one or many.

00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:31.830
Users are used to knowing
that when there's a circle,

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:35.190
you can select one and when there's
a square, you can select many.

00:17:35.190 --> 00:17:38.550
If you use other shapes,
it can get really confusing

00:17:38.550 --> 00:17:42.260
or if you reverse the functionality,
that is also confusing.

00:17:43.810 --> 00:17:48.190
Make sure that the form inputs
are still intuitive and behave

00:17:48.190 --> 00:17:49.680
in a recognizable way.

00:17:52.330 --> 00:17:53.940
You also want to make
sure that changing

00:17:53.940 --> 00:17:57.440
the style doesn't change the
behavior of the form element

00:17:57.440 --> 00:17:59.390
or break the functionality.

00:17:59.390 --> 00:18:04.340
Your styled form elements should
work the same way as unstyled

00:18:04.340 --> 00:18:07.770
form elements so that users
who can't see, who don't know

00:18:07.770 --> 00:18:12.270
that this looks different can
still interact with the form.

00:18:13.300 --> 00:18:18.598
For example, focus states,
it's really easy to forget

00:18:18.599 --> 00:18:20.560
about focus states.

00:18:20.560 --> 00:18:25.350
Designers often think they're
ugly, developers just forget

00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:27.580
that it's something
we need to deal with.

00:18:27.580 --> 00:18:31.110
Always test with the keyboard
and make sure that you have focus

00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:32.230
and active states.

00:18:33.620 --> 00:18:38.620
Here's an example of some code
that I found on w3schools.com,

00:18:38.620 --> 00:18:43.120
which is notorious for having a
lot of really bad code examples.

00:18:45.570 --> 00:18:49.330
If you're looking for code
examples, look at our resources

00:18:49.330 --> 00:18:53.050
because we've given you some
good functional examples.

00:18:53.050 --> 00:18:56.950
In this particular example,
they have restyled the checkbox,

00:18:56.950 --> 00:19:02.230
and the way they've done
it, they're basically hiding

00:19:02.230 --> 00:19:05.580
the existing checkbox and
replacing it with another one

00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:08.730
and there's no focus state.

00:19:08.730 --> 00:19:13.450
You can't tell in this little
video, but I am using a keyboard

00:19:13.450 --> 00:19:18.580
to interact with this form
and there's no indication

00:19:18.580 --> 00:19:22.200
of which checkbox is
active at the moment.

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:27.090
Actually, I messed with
the code on this to try

00:19:27.090 --> 00:19:29.640
to add a focus state to it, and
the way they've written that code,

00:19:29.640 --> 00:19:33.200
it is impossible to
add a focus state.

00:19:33.200 --> 00:19:37.890
Just be careful not to break the
functionality when you add styles.

00:19:40.030 --> 00:19:42.210
You also want to be
careful with dropdowns.

00:19:43.390 --> 00:19:48.850
It's really easy to style the
input, that initial box at the top

00:19:48.850 --> 00:19:51.990
of this demo, that styling the
drop-down menu that shows up

00:19:51.990 --> 00:19:55.990
when you click on it
is very difficult.

00:19:55.990 --> 00:20:01.450
It usually requires JavaScript and
it is usually not keyboard navigable.

00:20:02.690 --> 00:20:06.600
That dropdown might be really
ugly, but you're really better off

00:20:06.600 --> 00:20:10.760
leaving it alone and leaving it ugly
so that users can still interact

00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:11.644
with it.

00:20:13.490 --> 00:20:16.510
There is some browser default
behavior that you can change

00:20:16.510 --> 00:20:20.280
without hurting accessibility,
for example, fieldsets.

00:20:21.310 --> 00:20:25.950
Fieldsets look really ugly in
the browser but Rian will explain

00:20:25.950 --> 00:20:28.190
in a few minutes why
they're really important.

00:20:30.550 --> 00:20:33.510
This is what a form looks
like with field sets.

00:20:33.510 --> 00:20:36.890
With some pretty minimal
CSS, you can make field sets

00:20:36.890 --> 00:20:39.090
look like other inputs.

00:20:39.090 --> 00:20:41.490
It doesn't take much
to remove that border

00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:45.780
and scoot the legend
around a little bit.

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:50.050
If you have a form that has a mix
of field sets and regular fields,

00:20:50.050 --> 00:20:53.510
those fieldsets look extra weird.

00:20:53.510 --> 00:20:56.250
You can adjust the
behavior of field sets

00:20:56.250 --> 00:20:59.220
to make them look more
like the rest of the form.

00:21:01.850 --> 00:21:04.690
You should also make sure you
put the submit button at the end

00:21:04.690 --> 00:21:05.850
of the form.

00:21:05.850 --> 00:21:10.300
I know that sounds obvious but
this has become very common lately.

00:21:12.420 --> 00:21:16.880
Especially with like terms
and conditions or SMS consent.

00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:21.330
Users and especially
blind users will not see

00:21:21.330 --> 00:21:24.530
or read anything that happens
below the submit button

00:21:24.530 --> 00:21:27.680
because they think the submit
button is the end of the form.

00:21:27.680 --> 00:21:30.790
Don't put other information
under the button.

00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:33.350
This is a screenshot from Etsy.

00:21:33.350 --> 00:21:36.330
They've got that register
button and then underneath it,

00:21:36.330 --> 00:21:39.450
they have other options for
other ways you can sign in.

00:21:39.450 --> 00:21:45.090
Then below that,
they have some legalese saying that

00:21:45.090 --> 00:21:48.710
by registering you are agreeing
to their terms and conditions.

00:21:48.710 --> 00:21:53.300
A lot of users are
never going to see that.

00:21:53.300 --> 00:21:56.300
Make sure the submit button is always
the very last thing in the form.

00:21:59.300 --> 00:22:01.330
Don't hide labels.

00:22:01.330 --> 00:22:07.280
Labels need to always be visible and
placeholders do not replace labels.

00:22:07.280 --> 00:22:10.610
The placeholder goes away
as soon as you start typing.

00:22:10.610 --> 00:22:12.770
Now you don't know
what you're doing.

00:22:14.190 --> 00:22:16.900
Make sure that the
label is always visible.

00:22:19.180 --> 00:22:22.220
Error messages are
also very important.

00:22:22.220 --> 00:22:26.350
It's easy to forget that you
need to design error messages

00:22:26.350 --> 00:22:29.010
but you want to create some
space at the top of your form,

00:22:29.010 --> 00:22:32.400
so that you can display all of
the error messages in one place.

00:22:34.450 --> 00:22:37.910
You can use color to show
that there is an error.

00:22:37.910 --> 00:22:41.520
For instance, in this screenshot,
the error message is in red,

00:22:41.520 --> 00:22:45.650
but also use an icon or some
other indicator that doesn't rely

00:22:45.650 --> 00:22:49.440
on color so that people who can't
see color will still be able

00:22:49.440 --> 00:22:50.730
to tell that there's
something wrong.

00:22:52.540 --> 00:22:55.600
You want to make sure that the
text of the error message is clear

00:22:55.600 --> 00:22:57.290
and tells the users
what they need to do.

00:22:59.020 --> 00:23:01.310
Rian is going to talk some
more about error messages

00:23:01.310 --> 00:23:02.940
along with some other standards.

